  "grammar_point": {
    "title": "Chinese money: 块、毛、分",
    "explanation": "Spoken Chinese uses 块 (kuài) for yuan and 毛 (máo) for jiao (0.1 yuan). Written Chinese uses 元 and 角. To say prices: 五块三毛 = 5.30 yuan. Numbers over 100: 一百 = 100, 两百 = 200, 一千 = 1000. Note: use 两 (liǎng) not 二 (èr) when counting things.",
